31/03/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Defence Ministry Secretary of State George Cristian Maior said Tuesday (30 March) that Romanian and US officials will hold extensive talks during the coming months on the possible location of US bases in the country. 
He reiterated Romania's readiness to host US bases, especially now that it has become a full-fledged NATO member. 
Maior added that Romania is fully committed to its participation in NATO operations in Afghanistan and the Balkans. 
(Rompres - 30/03/04)
